House in my hometown. This kind of house build on the water is unique in Hong Kong and only find it in Tai O. This kind of house in the past old days are mainly for the fishermen. More than 10 years ago, a large fire burnt down a lot of this houses and left a few. This one is new and build after the fire.

House at my hometown. This 100 years old abandon house has a sad story. Before 1960's, this house is for isolate the serious sick or the one who got infectious diseases. At that time they'll isolate here and let them die naturally. Because at that time, the medical levels still very poor in Hong Kong not to mention my little village. Before 1970's, basically my village is isolate from the city, the transport is very poor and differcult. At that time, just 2 ways to city. One is take more than 3 hours ferry in the morning. The other way is walk more than an hour through the forest and than take one hour bus to a ferry pier. Take another 90 minutes by ferry to city. So at that time if you got any serious sick in my village, nothing you can do. Just isolate in this house where is situate in the mountain.
